Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum had 33 points and nine rebounds.
Payton Pritchard scored six points in overtime.
Jrue Holiday added 17 points and five assists.
Derrick White scored 14 and had six assists.
Cam Thomas reached 30 points for the fourth time this season, finishing with 31 points.

Cameron Johnson was fouled by Tatum after missing a wide open 3-point attempt in the closing seconds of regulation but grabbed his own miss and sank two free throws, tying it at 94 with 7.6 seconds to play.
Tatum missed a 3-pointer as time expired, sending the game to overtime.
Boston forced the Nets into a shot-clock violation before Pritchard was fouled and hit two free throws.
The Celtics were held below their league-leading average of 19 3-pointers made per game, shooting 14 for 53 from deep, while the Nets made 10 3-pointers.
Pre-Game Insights: Nets coach Jordi Fernandez mentioned it was going to be 'exciting because they like to run, too,' so they slowed Boston by picking up defensively deep in the backcourt most of the game.
The Celtics were coming off their first home loss of the season against Golden State.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Boston guard Jaylen Brown missed his fourth straight game with a strained left hip flexor.
Center Luke Kornet was also out because of right hamstring tightness.
The Celtics outscored the Nets 20-10 in transition.
